    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-2056772">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-2056772">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2056772)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2056772">
																		TL;DR: I love some of the subtleties and imageries, but the descriptions have a habit of going purple prose.
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/soullesssingularity" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(637830); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=637830&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183590" alt="SoullessSingularity" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=637830)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/soullesssingularity" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(637830); return false;" >SoullessSingularity</a></span> <span class="odate time_1403511825 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">23 Jun 2014 08:23</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2056772">
									

<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Click&nbsp;for&nbsp;Full&nbsp;Review</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Hide&nbsp;Full&nbsp;Review</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>and spoke in a voice like a loose bolt passing through a live steam turbine.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Me likey.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>their plain black ink stark in the soothing actinic glow of the single arc lamp that illuminated 25b</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I think this is pretty purple prose.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>he said, wetly</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is really awkward and I feel the description doesn't match the actual thing being said.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>she said through clenched brass teeth, &quot;which are decentralized. You even use,&quot; she spat,</p>
</blockquote>
<p>First she is saying, then she is spitting. This prose I feel can be tightened up here.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Chase- no, the Factory- spoke, and Its voice was pollution and waste- not Flesh, no, something far less comprehensible- the sound of a clock being smashed with a hammer, over and over and over and over-</p>
</blockquote>
<p>As much as I love the imagery, the excessive hyphen use throws me off a bit.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Above them, the twin spheres of the regulator creaked and moaned as they oxidized, little flakes of green tumbling into the expanding maw of the Factory.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I really like this.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>the fumes of industrial putrescence it poured forth with each irregular, laboured breath.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I like this significantly less.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The walls fell away, melting as they did so, and in their place a blackened, tar-sticky landscape like a cancerous lung after excision, and in it two ancient, ruined towers- one of bronze and smoke, one of translucent plastic and glowing lights.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Holy run-on sentence, batman.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Two ruined towers, tumbled and strewn across the sticky blackness of a planet that was heaving and sweating technology, machines birthing machines which ate themselves and made more, a purposeless cancer of ingenuity</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Didn't you just use the cancer allegory? Why use it again so soon? As much as I like &quot;a purposeless cancer of ingenuity&quot;, everything else just seems really&#8230; ham. I love some of this, it just goes too far into purple prose territory on occasion.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Camshaft seemed to stagger, a moment of organic weakness making him lean on the doorframe with one Standardized claw, its brassworks still bearing the remains of the sacred oils from the construction process.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I really love how subtle the sacred oil mentioning was and organic weakness. It really builds the culture and atmosphere without going ham. I really love it.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>She smiled, revealing a mouthful of steel teeth tipped with cutting diamonds.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I thought she had copper teeth?</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

							</div>

										<div class="signature">
					<hr class="signature-separator"/>
					

<p>Living the dream, or dreaming the life?</p>

				</div>
					
					
